main event: An observation of a large light, ten times the size of Venus at its brightest, was reported in Wenatchee, Washington.
interesting points: The light was observed for about 7 minutes using binoculars,The object was moving from south to north and went past the horizon,The conclusion suggested the observed object was probably the star Arcturus,This report was part of the Project Blue Book study on UFOs,The visibility was perfect with a clear sky at the time of the observation.
sighted object: a large white light with a silhouette
